comment:
Some context would be nice, instead of all this gossip.

If this is the newspaper appeal, isn't that over long ago? So how can there be another ruling? Which judge, in what court, for what offence? Some context please?

You can't appeal a ruling on press liable with information not relevant to the specific act of liable. You need another court case on some other offence. You can't just keep appealing the same case again and again when the underlying facts about what was printed have already been addressed.

Stop obfusticating criminal and civil action. Libel was a case against what was printed, not the criminal activity of assault or anything else. You can't appeal a libel case because the criminal case was or wasn't proven. All the newspaper has to prove is that it was true at the time of going to press and was adequately investigated to print what they did. If the facts change later the newspaper isn't to blame. They can't be expected to know the future or about any cover-up or perjury.

If the lawsuit between JD and AH had occurred first and then had JD gone after the Sun and DW, then he would have over turned the charges and then their publication would be full of lies and his case would have gone through.
